evidence: A function is a mathematical concept. It takes an input, processes it according to some rule, and produces an output.
A system is essentially the same idea, but we often use this term in engineering. We talk about inputs and outputs, and the system could be simple or complex.
A network is really just a more complex kind of system - one made up of many interconnected subsystems.
In electrical engineering, we often study electrical networks, where components like resistors, capacitors, and inductors are connected to form a circuit.

In modern artificial intelligence, we have neural networks, which connect many artificial neurons to process information - in some ways, similar to how biological neurons communicate through electrical signals in our nervous system.
